’s story reveals discrepancies between medical and legal definitions of a person’s mental state at the time of a crime. Murder and Madness on Trial bridges the micro-historical dimensions of Paolo’s murder case and the macro-historical perspectives on medical and legal evidence used to identify intermittent madness.A tragic and gripping tale, Murder and Madness on Trial allows readers to look “through a glass darkly” at early modern violence, madness, criminal justice, medical and legal expertise, and the construction and circulation of news. This erudite and engaging book will appeal to early modern historians and true crime fans alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aInsanity (Law)zItalyzBolognaxHistoryy16th century. 0aTrials (Murder)zItalyzBologna. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Italy.2bisacsh  aBologna.  aIsabella Caccianemici.  aPaolo Barbieri.  achronicle.  acriminal insanity.  adeception.  aearly modern Italy.  aemotions.  aevidence.  afama.  ainsanity.  ajustice in the Papal States.  alaw.  amariticide.  amedical and legal definitions of madness.  apublic opinion.  areputation.  atrue crime.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079775640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271096001?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271096001423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780